summary: This is a final travel voucher approval notification from the DOJ's E2 travel system for a trip related to the Epstein investigation. It documents expenses for a witness interview conducted in Beverly Hills, CA in February 2020.

events.title: Witness Interview Trip
events.description: A trip was conducted for the purpose of interviewing a witness as part of the Epstein investigation. The travel occurred from February 26 to February 29, 2020, with a destination of Beverly Hills, CA.

keyFacts: A travel voucher was approved for an Epstein investigation witness interview trip occurring February 26-29, 2020.
The trip destination was Beverly Hills, California.
The voucher total expenses were $1,059.52 against an estimated trip cost of $1,621.65.
The document indicates ongoing investigative activity in the Epstein case as of early 2020.
The voucher was processed through the DOJ's E2 travel system under reference ID V0008.
